Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_metric_page(25.10)                            create_metric_page(25.10)

Name
       create_metric_page - Creates a new metric page

Syntax
       create_metric_page

       [-help]

       [-after <page_name>]

       [-before <page_name>]

       [-format {html excel text}]

       -name <page_name>

       Creates a new metric page.

       Creation  of a metric page is the first step in creating a metric table
       for HTML display. After creating a metric page, you need to specify the
       heading for the metric table using the create_metric_table_heading com-
       mand. After specifying the metric table heading, you create the  metric
       table using the create_metric_table command.

Parameters
       -after <page_name>
              Specifies to insert after the page with this name.

              Date_type: string, optional

       -before <page_name>
              Specifies to insert before the page with this name.

              Date_type: string, optional

       -format {html excel text}
              Specifies configuration for the report_metric format.

              Date_type: enum, optional

       -help  Prints out the command usage.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man create_metric_page

       -name <page_name>
              Specifies  the  name  of  the  new  page.  The page name must be
              unique.

              Date_type: string, required

Examples
              * The following command creates the metric page, User.

                create_metric_page -name User

              *

                The following command creates the Test metric page  after  the
                Summary page.

                create_metric_page -after Summary -name Test

Related Information
              * create_metric_table_heading

              * create_metric_table

              * report_metric

